ecific page or range of pages in which the material appears. (March 2017)">page&#160;needed</span></a></i>]</sup><br />\n<sup id="cite_ref-Eurobarometer_Languages_52-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Eurobarometer_Languages-52">[52]</a></sup><sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability" title="Wikipedia:Verifiability"><span title="The material near this tag failed verification of its source citation(s). (March 2017)">not in citation given</span></a></i>]</sup></td>\n<td>Official language in: <a href="/wiki/Turkey" title="Turkey">Turkey</a>, <a href="/wiki/Cyprus" title="Cyprus">Cyprus</a>, <a href="/wiki/Northern_Cyprus" title="Northern Cyprus">Northern Cyprus</a><br />\nRecognized minority language in: <a href="/wiki/Bosnia_and_Herzegovina" title="Bosnia and Herzegovina">Bosnia and Herzegovina</a>, <a href="/wiki/Republic_of_Macedonia" title="Republic of Macedonia">Macedonia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Romania" title="Romania">Romania</a>, <a href="/wiki/Iraq" title="Iraq">Iraq</a>, <a href="/wiki/Greece" title="Greece">Greece</a>, <a href="/wiki/Republic_of_Kosovo" class="mw-redirect" title="Republic of Kosovo">Republic of Kosovo</a><br /></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/File:Map_of_Turkish_Language.png" class="image"><img alt="Map of Turkish Language.png" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Map_of_Turkish_Language.png/230px-Map_of_Turkish_Language.png" width="230" height="210" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Map_of_Turkish_Language.png/345px-Map_of_Turkish_Language.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Map_of_Turkish_Language.png/460px-Map_of_Turkish_Language.png 2x" data-file-width="1270" data-file-height="1161" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Italian_language" title="Italian language">Italian</a></td>\n<td>63&#160;M</td>\n<td>66 M<sup id="cite_ref-53" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-53">[53]</a></sup> to 85&#160;M<sup id="cite_ref-Italian_language_54-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Italian_language-54">[54]</a></sup></td>\n<td>Official language in: <a href="/wiki/Italy" title="Italy">Italy</a>, <a href="/wiki/Switzerland" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>, <a href="/wiki/San_Marino" title="San Marino">San Marino</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sovereign_Military_Order_of_Malta" title="Sovereign Military Order of Malta">Sovereign Military Order of Malta</a>, <a href="/wiki/Vatican_City" title="Vatican City">Vatican City</a>. Italian is relevant in countries affected by the <a href="/wiki/Italian_diaspora" title="Italian diaspora">Italian diaspora</a> and in former colonies and occupied territories of the <a href="/wiki/Italian_Empire" title="Italian Empire">Italian Empire</a>.</td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/File:Map_Italophone_World_-_updated.png" class="image"><img alt="Map Italophone World - updated.png" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Map_Italophone_World_-_updated.png/230px-Map_Italophone_World_-_updated.png" width="230" height="106" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Map_Italophone_World_-_updated.png/345px-Map_Italophone_World_-_updated.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Map_Italophone_World_-_updated.png/460px-Map_Italophone_World_-_updated.png 2x" data-file-width="1357" data-file-height="628" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Tamil_language" title="Tamil language">Tamil</a></td>\n<td>68&#160;M</td>\n<td>76&#160;M<sup id="cite_ref-55" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-55">[55]</a></sup></td>\n<td>Official language in: <a href="/wiki/Sri_Lanka" title="Sri Lanka">Sri Lanka</a>, <a href="/wiki/Singapore" title="Singapore">Singapore</a>, and Indian states of <a href="/wiki/Tamil_Nadu" title="Tamil Nadu">Tamil Nadu</a> and <a href="/wiki/Puducherry" title="Puducherry">Puducherry</a>.</td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/File:TamilPopulation-World.png" class="image"><img alt="TamilPopulation-World.png" src